   obtaining Internet Explorer." FF 156 (JA ____). Even as late as June
   1995, Microsoft was planning only "to include low-level Internet
   `plumbing,' . . . but not a browser, with Windows 95." FF 156-57 (JA
   ____); GX 125, 124 ("[Windows 95] contains all the plumbing you need to
